- `M 27.58,40.70`: This command moves the "pen" to the starting point (27.58, 40.70).
- `L 35.74,22.14`: This command draws a line from the current point to (35.74, 22.14).

  - `20.28,20.28`: The radii of the ellipse.
  - `293.73`: The x-axis rotation.
  - `0,1`: The large-arc-flag and sweep-flag.
  - `22.12,60.23`: The endpoint of the arc.
- `L 27.58,40.70`: This command draws a line back to the starting point (27.58, 40.70), closing the path.

The path consists of two lines and an arc, forming a closed shape. This shape resembles a sector, which is a portion of a circle bounded by two radii and an arc.

Therefore, the shape drawn by this SVG path element is a sector.
